rong>Or perhaps you\'re wondering who tells these stories?</strong>\r\n<a title=\"About Leo Sofer\" href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/about-leo-sofer/\">Find out more about me, Leo Sofer</a>, and what led me to this work.','The Power of Stories','','inherit','closed','closed','','54-revision-v1','','','2015-10-06 14:51:15','2015-10-06 14:51:15','',54,'http://sjh.tthtesting.co.uk/archives/65',0,'revision','',0),(1841,3,'2015-04-04 10:02:52','2015-04-04 10:02:52','<h3>A story inspired by Integral Coaching\r\nand created by intuitive storyteller Leo Sofer</h3>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1856\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Linda-logo-copy.jpg\" alt=\"Wisdom of the Whole Coaching Academy\" width=\"550\" height=\"248\" />\r\n<div class=\"intro\">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class=\"quote\">I met Leo when a mutual friend introduced us, and I was so inspired when I found out what his work does. He is re-inspiring the mythic level of consciousness, which can be such a powerful way of accessing change. Leos work is not only entertaining, it feels like a critical ingredient...</div>\r\n<div class=\"quoter\"><img class=\"wp-image-1855 alignnone\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Linda-pic-copy.jpg\" alt=\"Linda Bark\" width=\"110\" height=\"144\" />Linda Bark</div>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<h3>\"The Insight Bird\" Story Synopsis</h3>\r\nTheir relationship was mostly delicious and easy; friends would often comment on how great they looked together. But there would be times when the smooth road would become a forest of tangled briars and sharp thorns, and each of them would get caught in their darkest fears.\r\n\r\nOne day, stuck in what seemed like the densest, thorniest tangle yet, she ran to her bedroom and burst into tears. Just then, she heard the familiar sound of thrumming wings and the tapping of a bird\'s beak on wood, coming from inside the wardrobe....\r\n\r\n<strong>If you are involved in Integral Coaching, as a coach, student or client, you will find this 30 minute audio story relevant to your own process. Listening to it will...</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>help you get a felt sense of how Integral Coaching can resolve problems by shifting your level of consciousness.</li>\r\n	<li>give you a mythic way of understanding the process of insight, learning and growth.  The more familiar you become with the mythic, the more you can bring its perspective to bear on whatever challenges you face.</li>\r\n	<li>be fun and entertaining to listen to!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Leo-in-Sardinia-closer-still1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-1475\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Leo-in-Sardinia-closer-still1.jpg\" alt=\"Leo Sofer\" width=\"119\" height=\"114\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Leo Sofer has been telling stories since 1989</strong> and has developed Intuitive Storytelling as a way of accessing our inherent wisdom and expressing it in story form. He has worked with thousands of people over the last 25 years, telling stories and leading trainings in Intuitive Storytelling.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class=\"quote\">Leos stories offer a delicious way to reconnect with what matters most in our lives. They seem to arise out of the mystical heart of humanity, gently and kindly tapping our yearning for truth and leading us, with good humour, straight to the heart of our spiritual questions.</div>\r\n<span class=\"quoter\">Danica Shoan Ankele,\r\nProgram Director, WZEN.org</span></blockquote>','The Insight Bird','','publish','closed','closed','','the-insight-bird','','','2015-10-06 17:20:10','2015-10-06 17:20:10','',1926,'http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/?page_id=1841',1,'page','',0),(1843,3,'2015-04-04 10:16:00','2015-04-04 10:16:00','<h3>A story inspired by Integral Coaching\nand created by intuitive storyteller Leo Sofer.</h3>\n\nTheir relationship was mostly delicious and easy; friends would often comment on how great they looked together. But there would be times when the smooth road would become a forest of tangled briars and sharp thorns, and each of them would get caught in their darkest fears.\n\nOne day, stuck in what seemed like the densest, thorniest tangle yet, she ran to her bedroom and burst into tears. Just then, she heard the familiar sound of thrumming wings and the tapping of a bird\'s beak on wood, coming from inside the wardrobe...\n\n<a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/LeoSofer-TheInsightBird.mp3\">LeoSofer-TheInsightBird</a>\n\n&nbsp;','The Insight Bird - Download','','publish','closed','closed','','2do4guhfla3085jdkw','','','2015-10-06 15:26:30','2015-10-06 15:26:30','',1926,'http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/?page_id=1843',2,'page','',0),(1922,3,'2015-06-15 20:53:51','2015-06-15 20:53:51','<h3>A Healing Journey</h3>\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1953\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/David-and-Susan-logo.jpg\" alt=\"David and Susan logo\" width=\"187\" height=\"48\" /></h3>\n<div class=\"intro\">\n\n\"We trust Leo with our hearts and the essence of our work. We share him with you so that you may benefit as well. We invite you to not only listen to our Story from Leo to explore more stories of rich wisdom and delight at his website.\"\n\nDavid and Susan.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1954\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/David-and-Susan-pic.jpg\" alt=\"David and Susan pic\" width=\"575\" height=\"250\" />\n\n</div>\n<h3>\"The Queen of the Sea\" Story Synopsis</h3>\nShe\'d only visited the doctors office for something minor, but as soon as he came back into the room, she could see from his face that something really serious was up. As he spoke, it was as if his words faded into the background after the first few sentences. She was no longer listening because she had gone into shock.\n\n<img class=\"alignright size-thumbnail wp-image-1970\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/The-Queen-of-the-Sea-drawing-small-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"The Queen of the Sea\" width=\"150\" height=\"150\" />Sometime later she found herself sitting by the sea, in deep reverie. Far off in the distance the woman saw a light, coming closer all the time. A cresting wave? A shaft of reflected sunlight? No. The Queen of the sea had come for her, riding her watery chariot. And she took her away and down to her underwater palace and showed her all the ways she\'d walked away from herself and towards something that was not true.\n\n<strong>If you have faced, or are facing, the kind of emergency that shocking health news can bring, then this story 34 minute audio story will help you...</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>drop to a deeper level inside yourself, and start to look at your challenges mythologically, allowing for greater access to your own inner wisdom</li>\n	<li>See the gifts in your situation by giving you a larger perspective on it</li>\n	<li>Open to your sense of possibility and power in the midst of stormy waters</li>\n	<li>Be fun and entertaining to listen to!</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Here\'s what one of our clients said about listening to this story</h3>\n<div class=\"intro\">\"Dearest Susan and David,\nI took the time when my mind was fresh to submerge myself into this story. What imagery. What grief and gratitude I felt as I rode with and as her. Truly I thank you, for sharing such a precious gem. I will be listening again and again! Great story telling! A real soul feeder.\"\n<strong>Mignon Mead-Shikaly</strong></div>\n<strong>Leo Sofer has been telling stories since 1989 and has developed Intuitive Storytelling as a way of accessing our inherent wisdom and expressing it in story form. He has worked with thousands of people over the last 25 years, telling stories and leading trainings in Intuitive Storytelling.</strong>\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"quote\">Leos stories offer a delicious way to reconnect with what matters most in our lives. They seem to arise out of the mystical heart of humanity, gently and kindly tapping our yearning for truth and leading us, with good humour, straight to the heart of our spiritual questions.</div>\n<span class=\"quoter\">Danica Shoan Ankele, Program Director, WZEN.org</span></blockquote>','The Queen of the Sea','','publish','closed','closed','','the-queen-of-the-sea','','','2015-10-06 15:26:30','2015-10-06 15:26:30','',1926,'http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/?page_id=1922',5,'page','',0),(1923,3,'2015-06-15 20:57:49','2015-06-15 20:57:49','<h3>A story inspired by The Living Medicine Project\nand created by intuitive storyteller Leo Sofer</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2006\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Garliq-logo.jpg\" alt=\"Garliq logo\" width=\"144\" height=\"147\" />\n\nThe mans son lay dying, and all the doctors and all the medicines had been no use at all. At the end of his rope, and willing to go beyond what he knew, he turned to the land for healing.\n\nAfter many days and nights in the forest, something miraculous began to happen: the land began to sing its song through him. Later, holding his son in his arms and singing this song, he began at last to see the colour return to the boys cheeks\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-2009\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/The-Song-of-the-Land-drawing-reoriented-copy-270x300.jpg\" alt=\"The Song of the Land drawing, reoriented copy\" width=\"270\" height=\"300\" /><strong>Play or download the story here</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/LeoSofer-TheSongOfTheLand.mp3\">LeoSofer - The Song Of The Land</a>\n\nFind out more about Leo\'s work at <a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Stories of the Journey Home</a>','The Song of the Land - Download','','publish','closed','closed','','40s45ughaewfosn','','','2015-10-06 15:26:30','2015-10-06 15:26:30','',1926,'http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/?page_id=1923',12,'page','',0),(1926,3,'2015-06-15 21:23:49','2015-06-15 21:23:49','','Collaborators','','publish','closed','closed','','collaborators','','','2015-10-06 15:26:30','2015-10-06 15:26:30','',0,'http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/?page_id=1926',49,'page','',0),(1988,3,'2015-09-16 16:08:48','2015-09-16 16:08:48','<h3>A story inspired by The Living Medicine Project\nand created by intuitive storyteller Leo Sofer</h3>\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2006\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/Garliq-logo.jpg\" alt=\"Garliq logo\" width=\"144\" height=\"147\" />\n<h3></h3>\n<div class=\"intro\">\n\n\"<em>While this story has great beauty in it\'s simplicity and the enchanted worlds it evokes, that wasn\'t what touched really got to me.</em>\n\n<em>Honestly, I wept the second time I listened.  Tears of joy and sadness, relief and hope poured down my cheeks, straight from my heart.</em>\n\n<em>It was the remembering that hit me. Remembering our place in the web of life and the love from our Mother Earth.Thank you, Leo.</em> \"\n\nGarliq, Owner, The Living Medicine Project.\n<a href=\"http://livingmedicineproject.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.livingmedicineproject.com</a>\n\n</div>\n<h3><img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-2018\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/The-Song-of-the-Land-drawing-cropped-and-reoriented-300x274.jpg\" alt=\"The Song of the Land drawing, cropped and reoriented\" width=\"238\" height=\"217\" /></h3>\n<h3>\"The Song of the Land\" Story Synopsis</h3>\nThe man\'s son lay dying, and all the doctors and all the medicines had been no use at all. At the end of his rope, and willing to go beyond what he knew, he turned to the land for healing.\n\nAfter many days and nights in the forest, something miraculous began to happen: the land began to sing its song through him. Later, holding his son in his arms and singing this song, he began at last to see the colour return to the boy\'s cheeks...\n<h3></h3>\n<strong>Leo Sofer has been telling stories since 1989 and has developed Intuitive Storytelling as a way of accessing our inherent wisdom and expressing it in story form. He has worked with thousands of people over the last 25 years, telling stories and leading trainings in Intuitive Storytelling.</strong>\n<blockquote>\n<div class=\"quote\">Leos stories offer a delicious way to reconnect with what matters most in our lives. They seem to arise out of the mystical heart of humanity, gently and kindly tapping our yearning for truth and leading us, with good humour, straight to the heart of our spiritual questions.</div>\n<span class=\"quoter\">Danica Shoan Ankele, Program Director, WZEN.org</span></blockquote>','The Song of the Land','','publish','closed','closed','','the-song-of-the-land','','','2015-10-06 15:26:30','2015-10-06 15:26:30','',1926,'http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/?page_id=1988',10,'page','',0),(1990,3,'2015-09-16 16:18:30','2015-09-16 16:18:30','<h3>A story inspired by the work of <a href=\"http://www.wisdomrx.com/\">Wisdom Rx</a>\nand created by intuitive storyteller Leo Sofer</h3>\n[caption id=\"attachment_1954\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"358\"]<a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/David-and-Susan-pic.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-1954\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/David-and-Susan-pic-300x130.jpg\" alt=\"David Mackenzie and Susan Perkins of Wisdom Rx\" width=\"358\" height=\"157\" /></a> David Mackenzie and Susan Perkins of Wisdom Rx[/caption]\n\nShe\'d only visited the doctors office for something minor, but as soon as he came back into the room, she could see from his face that something really serious was up. As he spoke, it was as if his words faded into the background after the first few sentences. She was no longer listening because she had gone into shock.\n\nSometime later she found herself sitting by the sea, in deep reverie.\n\n<a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/The-Queen-of-the-Sea-drawing-small.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-1970\" src=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/The-Queen-of-the-Sea-drawing-small-300x275.jpg\" alt=\"The Queen of the Sea\" width=\"300\" height=\"275\" /></a>Far off in the distance the woman saw a light, coming closer all the time. A cresting wave? A shaft of reflected sunlight? No. The Queen of the sea had come for her, riding her watery chariot. And she took her away and down to her underwater palace and showed her all the ways she\'d walked away from herself and towards something that was not true.\n\nBy the time the Queen of the Sea had finished with her, she was all clean and pure and completely herself. She had been brought back to the true self she\'d always been, stripped of all the things she\'d mistakenly taken to be herself.\n\nAnd then she knew what she needed to do. She went to her husband and her friends and her relatives and she found the words to say all the things that she should have said long ago. She said what had always been hers to say, and was received with great gratitude.\n\nAnd then she realised there was another One that also needed her apology. One so close, she had scarcely noticed him. And yet one so essential that to be apart from him another moment was painful for her...\n\n<strong>Play or download the story here</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.storiesofthejourneyhome.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06//LeoSofer-TheQueenOfTheSea.mp3\">LeoSofer - The Queen of the Sea</a>','The Queen of the Sea - Download','','publish','closed','closed','','90fjalfk9eogjojaw49gm'